  "type": "spell",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"ddb\">\n<p>Flames race across your body, shedding bright light in a 30-foot radius and dim light for an additional 30 feet for the spell’s duration. The flames don’t harm you. Until the spell ends, you gain the following benefits:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>You are immune to &amp;Reference[fire]{fire} damage and have resistance to &amp;Reference[cold]{cold} damage.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Any creature that moves within 5 feet of you for the first time on a turn or ends its turn there takes 1d10 &amp;Reference[fire]{fire} damage.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>You can use your action to create a &amp;Reference[line]{line} of &amp;Reference[fire]{fire} 15 feet long and 5 feet wide extending from you in a direction you choose. Each creature in the &amp;Reference[line]{line} must make a &amp;Reference[dex]{Dexterity} saving throw. A creature takes 4d8 &amp;Reference[fire]{fire} damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>",
